.TH TRAY 1 "2026-04-18" "systray 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tray \- system tray helper for shell scripts
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tray
.I command
[options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
tray is a small Rust daemon and CLI for showing Status Notifier tray items from shell scripts and other automation.

The daemon is started on demand by
.B tray show
and exits automatically when the last tray item is removed.
.B tray list
and
.B tray hide
do not start the daemon if it is not already running.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B show
Create or update a tray item.
At least one of
.B --icon
or
.B --tooltip
is required.
.TP
.B hide
Remove a tray item by id.
If the id does not exist, the command fails with a non-zero exit code.
.TP
.B list
Print the ids of active tray items, one per line.
If the daemon is not running, this returns successfully with no output.
.TP
.B run
Show a tray item while executing a command, then hide the item when the command exits.
The command is passed after
.B -- .
.TP
.B daemon
Run the background daemon directly.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --id " " ID
Item id used to create, update, or hide a tray entry.
.TP
.BR --icon " " PATH
Path to a PNG or SVG icon file.
.TP
.BR --tooltip " " TEXT
Tooltip text for the tray item.
.TP
.BR --on-click " " CMD
Shell command to run when the item is activated.
.TP
.BR --pid " " PID
PID associated with the tray item. The daemon can hide items when the process exits.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Controls log level. Defaults to
.B error
when unset.
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Used to locate the Unix socket for the client and daemon.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/tray.sock
Default socket path when
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
is set.
.TP
.I /tmp/tray-<uid>/tray.sock
Fallback socket path when
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
is unavailable.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B non-zero
An error occurred, such as an invalid command, missing tray item, daemon startup failure, or command failure in
.B run .
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show a tooltip-only tray entry:
.EX
tray show --id example --tooltip "Example item"
.EE
.TP
Show a tray entry with an icon:
.EX
tray show --id example --icon /path/to/icon.png --tooltip "Example item"
.EE
.TP
Show a tray entry bound to the current shell process:
.EX
tray show --id shell --tooltip "Shell task running" --pid "$$"
.EE
.TP
Remove an item:
.EX
tray hide --id example
.EE
.TP
List active items:
.EX
tray list
.EE
.TP
Run a command with a temporary tray icon:
.EX
tray run --icon media-record --id app -- sleep 50
.EE
.SH NOTES
The
.B --on-click
command is executed through
.BR sh (1)
with
.BR -lc ,
so it should be treated as shell code.
The
.B run
subcommand forwards
.B SIGINT
and
.B SIGTERM
to the wrapped command.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR sh (1)
